cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on understanding image representations, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes methods to establish mathematical properties of representations, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of structured-output regression, which is a subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper applies its theoretical findings to popular representations, which involves analyzing and comparing different models (cs.MM).
